data.text: Leads TXT 3865076300 1979 Honda CB750K 10th Anniversary Limited Edition at No Reserve: This 1979 Honda CB750K is a 10th Anniversary Limited Edition example that spent time with a single owner in California before its 2022 acquisition by the seller, reportedly following over two decades in storage. Subsequent recommissioning work is said to have included overhauling the four Keihin carburetors, flushing the brake fluid, and changing the battery. Powered by a 749cc DOHC inline-four paired with a five-speed transmission, the motorcycle is finished in two-tone maroon and red with gold pinstriping, chrome fenders, and 10th Anniversary badges. It also features a stepped two-up seat, an electric starter, a chrome four-into-four exhaust system, a front disc brake, ComStar cast alloy wheels, and both center and side stands. This CB750K is offered at no reserve with a tool kit and a clean California title in the seller's name. http://dlvr.it/TB8Kbd Bringatrailer.com #carsofinstagram #carporn #classiccar
